assessment_items.question_content:
Tariq and Lucia are finalists in a baking competition. For the final round, each of them will randomly select a card *without replacement* that will reveal what their primary flavor must be. Here are the available cards:

$\begin{array}{ccc}
\boxed{\text{Chocolate}} & \boxed{\text{Vanilla}} & \boxed{\text{Lemon}}
\\
\boxed{\text{Raspberry}} & \boxed{\text{Strawberry}} & \boxed{\text{Coffee}}
\end{array}$

Tariq wants to get lemon, and Lucia wants to get coffee. Tariq will draw first, followed by Lucia. 

**What is the probability that both contestants get the ingredient they want?**  
*Round your answer to two decimal places.*

[[☃ numeric-input 1]]

hints:
###Multiplication rule

$\begin{align}
P(\text{Both get what they want})&=\blueE{\dfrac{1}{6}} \cdot \maroonD{\dfrac{1}{5}}
\\\\
&=\dfrac{1}{30}
\\\\
&\approx 0.03
\end{align}$

###Multiplication rule

$\begin{align}
P(\text{Both correct})&=\blueE{\dfrac{2}{5}} \cdot \maroonD{\dfrac{1}{4}}
\\\\
&=\dfrac{1}{10} \text{ or } 0.1
\end{align}$

###Multiplication rule

$\begin{align}
P(1^{\text{st}} \, \text{correct AND } 2^{\text{nd}} \, \text{incorrect})&=\blueE{\dfrac{2}{5}} \cdot \maroonD{\dfrac{3}{4}}
\\\\
&=\dfrac{3}{10} \text{ or } 0.3
\end{align}$

assessment_items.question_content:
Sammy and Hannah are finalists in a cooking competition. For the final round, each of them will randomly select a card *without replacement* that will reveal what their star ingredient must be. Here are the available cards:

$\begin{array}{ccc}
\boxed{\text{Cabbage}} & \boxed{\text{Spinach}} & \boxed{\text{Kale}}
\\
\boxed{\text{Leeks}} & \boxed{\text{Carrots}} & \boxed{\text{Turnips}}
\end{array}$

Sammy and Hannah both want to get leeks as their star ingredient. Sammy will draw first, followed by Hannah. 

**What is the probability that NEITHER contestant draws leeks?**  
*Round your answer to two decimal places.*

[[☃ numeric-input 1]]

hints:
###Multiplication rule

$\begin{align}
P(\text{Neither get leeks})&=\blueE{\dfrac{5}{6}} \cdot \maroonD{\dfrac{4}{5}}
\\\\
&=\dfrac{20}{30}
\\\\
&\approx 0.67
\end{align}$

###Multiplication rule

$\begin{align}
P(\text{Neither left-handed})&=\blueE{\dfrac{44}{50}} \cdot \maroonD{\dfrac{43}{49}}
\\\\
&=\dfrac{946}{1225}
\\\\
&\approx 0.772
\end{align}$
